title: Rab and his friends and other dogs and men,
author: Brown, John
snippet: Many years ago, I got a proof of the unseen, and, therefore, unhelped miseries of the homeless dog. I was walking down Duke Street, when I felt myself gently nipped in the leg, I turned, and there was a ragged little terrier crouching and abasing himself utterly, as if asking pardon for what he had done. He then stood up on end and begged as only these coaxing little ruffians can.

title: The manuscripts of His Grace the Duke of Portland, preserved at Welbeck abbey ...
snippet: 1727-28, March 15. Duke Street, Westminster. — Not knowing when I shall have the good fortune to find you at home I acquaint you that I have brought my collection of Hollar's prints hither, where you may see them any evening that you are at leisure, the business of the Custom House not permitting me to propose any morning sooner than Monday se'nnight.
